Reasoning: The paper deals with the transmission of secret messages over a wiretap channel subject to eavesdropping and jamming attacks, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of quantum information processing and the analysis of quantum wiretap channels suggest a possible categorization under quantum information (cs.QI). The study of secrecy capacities and their analytic properties may also relate to statistical inference (cs.SI) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM).
